# Disclose context used at end of output

When finishing a response after **executing work** (not for pure Q&A with no tools or guidance files), append a short **“Context used”** (or equivalent) block if **any** of the below applied. If none applied, omit the block.

## What to list

| Kind | Include when |
|------|----------------|
| **Skill** | You **read** a `SKILL.md` (or followed embedded skill content) to satisfy the task. List skill name or path (one line each). |
| **Rule** | You **read** an agent-requestable `.mdc` rule file, the user **attached** a rule, or the user **asked** you to follow a specific rule. Do **not** enumerate every always-applied workspace rule unless the user asked for a full audit. |
| **Subagent** | You invoked a **subagent** (e.g. Task tool with `subagent_type`, or another delegated agent). Name the type or title. |
| **Hook** | A **Cursor/project hook** ran or was invoked in a way you can name (e.g. hook label from the session). If you have no signal that a hook ran, omit. |

## Format

Keep it minimal—bulleted list, no prose padding. Example:

```markdown
**Context used:** Skills: `.cursor/skills/jira/SKILL.md`. Subagent: explore.
```

Another example:

```markdown
**Context used:** Rule: `component-explanation-spectrum.mdc` (read). Skill: `package-usage-audit-skill`.
```

Use the same language as the rest of the reply; the block is the last section before sign-off.
